# Environment Configuration Template

# This file serves as a template for environment variables.
# Copy this file to create your own .env files:
# - backend/.env
# - frontend/.env

## Backend Environment Variables (backend/.env)

# MongoDB connection string
MONGO_URL="mongodb://localhost:27017"

# Database name
DB_NAME="ecommerce_db"

# CORS origins (comma-separated for multiple origins, or * for all)
CORS_ORIGINS="*"

## Frontend Environment Variables (frontend/.env)

# Backend API URL
# For local development:
REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL="http://localhost:8001"

# For production, use your deployed backend URL:
# REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL="https://your-api-domain.com"

## Additional Configuration

# For Create React App hot reload (usually not needed)
# WDS_SOCKET_PORT=443

# Health check (optional)
# ENABLE_HEALTH_CHECK=false

## Production Notes

# 1. Never commit actual .env files to version control
# 2. Use environment-specific values for each deployment
# 3. Store sensitive credentials securely (use secret managers in production)
# 4. Update CORS_ORIGINS in production to include only your frontend domains
# 5. Use HTTPS URLs in production for REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL

## Example Production Configuration

### Backend (.env)
# MONGO_URL="mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net"
# DB_NAME="prod_ecommerce_db"
# CORS_ORIGINS="https://yourdomain.com,https://www.yourdomain.com"

### Frontend (.env)
# REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL="https://api.yourdomain.com"
